SET TO OPEN NEW TERMINALS IN CURRENT ACTIVE SCREEN :export DISPLAY=:0

OPEN NEW TERMINAL WINDOW : gnome-terminal


CRON : 

    LIST SCHEDULED CRON JOBS : crontab -l

    SCHEDULE CRON JOBS : crontab -e

    DENY USER TO EDIT CRON FILE : 
        
        FILE LOCATION : sudo vi /etc/cron.deny 
        
        ADD LINES : UserName

    DELETE ALL CRON JOBS : crontab -r


ANACRON : 

    CHECK BUILT IN CRON FOLDERS : ls /etc/cron*

    CREATE OR DELETE OR EDIT ANACRON FILE : cd /etc/cron.daily/Filename

    CREATE DAILY ANANCRON JOB (ONLY ROOT USER): vi /etc/anacron.daily/Filename

    CREATE WEEKLY ANANCRON JOB (ONLY ROOT USER): vi /etc/anacron.weekly/Filename

    CREATE MONTHLY ANANCRON JOB (ONLY ROOT USER): vi /etc/anacron.monthly/Filename

    CREATE YEARLY ANANCRON JOB (ONLY ROOT USER): vi /etc/anacron.yearly/Filename

    CHECK ANACRON DEFAULT TIMINGS : cat /etc/crontab

    CHECK OR CHANGE LAST TIMINGS OF ANACRON JOB RUN : sudo vi /var/spool/anacron/Filename 

    SEE ANACRON CONFIGURATION FILE : cat /etc/anacrontab


AT : 

    CHECK SERVICE STATUS : sudo systemctl status atd

    CHECK SCHEDULED AT JOBS : atq

    RUN AFTER N MINUTES FROM NOW : at now +5 minutes

    RUN SCRIPT : at -f /Path/To/Filename HH:MM 

    DELETE AT JOB : atrm JobID


SYSTEMD TIMER : 

    CREATE A SERVICE IN : sudo vi /etc/systemd/system/YourServiceName.service

    RELOAD SERVICE TO SYSTEMD : sudo systemctl daemon-reload

    RUN SERVICE : sudo systemctl start ServiceName.service

    STOP SERVICE : sudo systemctl stop ServiceName.service

    CREATE SYSTEMD TIMER : sudo vi /etc/systemd/system/YourServiceName.timer

    RUN TIMER : sudo systemctl start ServiceName.timer

    LIST OF ALL TIMERS :  systemctl list-timers

